description.narrative:
Jhpiego’s CDC award 1414 supports activities in Eastern, Southern and Western Provinces.  Under this award, Jhpiego supports the MOH, National HIV/AIDS/STI/TB Council (NAC) and the Zambia Defense Forces (ZDF) to operationalize Zambia’s response to the HIV/AIDS epidemic.  Under this project, Jhpiego supports:
1) delivery of voluntary medical male circumcision (VMMC), Prevention of Mother to Child Transmission (PMTCT), pediatric and adult HIV treatment and counseling and testing (CT) services;
2) expansion of strategic information through scale up of SmartCare;
3) integration of tuberculosis and HIV (TB/HIV) services.
